b"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":13},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39618","n39619","n39620"]}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to vow, to pledge","examples":[{"text":"إِنِّي نَذَرْتُ لِلرَّحْمَٰنِ صَوْمًا فَلَنْ أُكَلِّمَ الْيَوْمَ إِنسِيًّا","english":"Lo! I have vowed a fast unto the Beneficent, and may not speak today to any mortal."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to devote one's son to the service of God"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to place in front of a combat"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to see the danger, to see through the intentions of an enemy and be on one's guard"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make a vow to, profess before, profess a belief"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a vow; verbal noun of نَذَرَ (naḏara, “to vow, to warn”) (form I)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"anything consecrated to God","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pious gift; present to superiors","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pious gift; mulct for wounds","tags":["broadly"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"warning, admonition, threat, irregular verbal noun of أَنْذَرَ (ʔanḏara) (form IV)","examples":[{"text":"وَلَقَدْ جَاءَ آلَ فِرْعَوْنَ النُّذُرُ كَذَّبُوا بِآيَاتِنَا","english":"And warning came to the house of the Pharaoh that they reproved."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of نَذْر (naḏr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of نَذِير (naḏīr)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَذِرَ (naḏira) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Akin to Aramaic נִדְרָא (niḏrā), Classical Syriac ܢܕܪܐ (neḏrā), Hebrew נֶדֶר (néḏer), Punic 𐤍𐤃𐤓 (ndr) and Ugaritic 𐎐𐎄𐎗 (ndr). It is argued that the sense vow is influenced from Jewish and Christian usage in Aramaic and Hebrew, the sense of “warning” as in أَنْذَرَ (ʔanḏara) and its verbal noun نُذُر (nuḏur) being more particular to Arabic, so the original meaning of the base stem needs to have been “to take heed”.\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":null}